ce:section.ce:para:
Generally, having functional groups such as –NH, OH, C-O on the surface of G-CDs made a favorable sensing platform for hydrogen bonding. Interactions with amino acids and anions could change electronic properties due to the alternation of the fluorescence intensity. Therefore, the selectivity of the G-CDs + Cu2+ toward different amino acids containing alanine, arginine, cysteine, glycine, glutamine, lysine, tryptophan, tyrosine, valine was examined. As it can be seen (Fig. 9
                        ), upon the addition of C2O4
                        2−, the fluorescence intensity gradually recovered and reached a maximum intensity, although no apparent changes were observed in the case of additional amino acid.
